gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.calculation

Class HistoricalCalculation

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.calculation.HistoricalCalculation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @Entity
public final class HistoricalCalculation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

    Encapsulates data from a past calculation. Stores calculation metadata (division, specialty name, etc.), but does not store the actual risk results. Unlike CalculationResult, this class stores its data as primitive values and is suitable for storing in a database.

    This class presents an immutable public interface.

    Per Effective Java Item 17, this class is marked final because it was not designed for inheritance.
